Privacy Policy
Effective date: June 12, 2022


Collection and Use of Personal Information
  - Personal information is data that can be used to identify or contact a single person.

What personal information we collect
  - We don’t collect any personal information.

How we use your personal information
  - We don’t use any personal information.

Protection of Personal Information
  - We take the security of personal information very seriously. So, we decided not to collect any personal information.

Disclosure of image data
  - Image data is not and will not be disclosed to any third party.

Sharing of image data
  - Image data is not and will not be shared with any third party.

Collection and retention of image data
  - Image data is only temporarily collected and stored in the app's working memory for the duration of the processing 
    (from when a photo is selected to when the resulting screen gets dismissed or the app gets terminated). 
    After the user interaction with the photo is done, all references to the image data get removed from memory. 
    Other that that, image data is not stored or retained anywhere else, in any way.

Payments
  - We may provide paid products and/or services within the Service. In that case, we use third-party services for payment processing 
    (e.g. payment processors).
  - We will not store or collect payment details. That information is provided directly to our third-party payment processors 
    whose use of your personal information is governed by their Privacy Policy.


The payment processors we work with are:
  - Apple Store In-App Payments -- their Privacy Policy can be viewed at https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/en-ww/


We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time.
